Groundwater levels

Groundwater levels were obtained from United States Geological Survey (USGS) National Groundwater Monitoring Network for Platte River Basin in Nebraska from 2000 to 2018. 12 groundwater wells were selected based on data available, and screen depth. Read the data containing groundwater levels with missing values

Stream gauge height data

Stream gauge heights were obtained from USGS National Water Information System (NWIS) for Platte River Basin in Nebraska from 2000 to 2018. There were 12 gauge stations in the study area that contained data in the aforementioned period with some missing values. The stream gauge height data are given such as:

Precipitation data

Stream gauge heights were obtained from USGS National Water Information System (NWIS) for Platte River Basin in Nebraska from 2000 to 2018. There were 12 gauge stations in the study area that contained data in the aforementioned period with some missing values. The stream gauge height data are given such as:

# Pumping data The pumping data was obtained from the CENEB Groundwater model report prepared by Nebraska Department of Natural Resources. The time period is from Jan 2000 to Dec 2012.
